<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-397-572  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 397 572.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  April 23 1990 n464 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>EC rejects U.S. call for talks: Europeans do not see need forbilateral high-tech discussions. (European Community)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Peterson, Stacey; Bernier, Linda.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The European Community (EC) refuses to launch new high-technologynegotiations with the US while the General Agreement on Tariffsand Trade (GATT) talks are in progress.andP;  GATT, a multinationaltrade body, will conclude its current talks in December, 1990.andO;Some observers in the US computer industry believe the EC'sresistance to other high-tech talks may be a negotiating ploy,designed to put the US at a disadvantage if it pursues the needfor talks.andP;  US reasons for the talks differ from the EC's aims andobjectives.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     International TradeNegotiationInternational OrganizationsEuropean Community.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>